CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1952, pg. 2, reads: "Rev. Brewster's Car Bricked - The Rev. Mr. Brewster won the second confirmation from Common Pleas Court last week that he is still recognized by the court as the pastor of both sections of his feuding congregation at Calvary Baptist Church. Shortly after the decision was rendered some anonymous person threw bricks at his parked Cadillac leaving the above damage. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cadillac car with smashed windshield, owned by Rev. Brewster of Calvary Baptist Church, parked in residential street
